#: ../../finetuning/finetune.rst:148 fb663d1e6a3141d59d7053c212c9ae9b
msgid "**LoRA vs Full Fine-Tuning at a glance:**"
msgstr "**LoRA 与全量微调一览：**"

#: ../../finetuning/finetune.rst:150 dcd5647913b24384b04ec88ec1a5831f
#, python-format
msgid ""
"In internal benchmarks on single-speaker cloning, LoRA (``r=32``) "
"achieved approximately 98% of the speaker similarity of full fine-tuning,"
" while using roughly half the VRAM and producing checkpoint files that "
"are orders of magnitude smaller. LoRA is the recommended starting point "
"for most tasks. Results may vary with different datasets and goals."
msgstr ""
"在内部单说话人克隆基准上，LoRA（``r=32``）的说话人相似度约为全量微调的 98%，显存约减半，checkpoint "
"体积也小几个数量级。多数任务建议从 LoRA 起步；不同数据与目标下结果会有差异。"

#: ../../finetuning/finetune.rst:157 bff7d67f001f459496a585952c03e3f2
msgid "LoRA Fine-Tuning"
msgstr "LoRA Fine-Tuning"

#: ../../finetuning/finetune.rst:159 85ce36c8d1204b538a887adc1d3cfba7
#, python-format
msgid ""
"LoRA trains a small number of additional parameters (typically < 1% of "
"the model) while keeping the base model frozen. It is the recommended "
"starting point for most fine-tuning tasks."
msgstr "LoRA 在冻结基座的前提下，仅训练少量附加参数（通常 < 模型参数的 1%）。多数微调任务建议从此入手。"

#: ../../finetuning/finetune.rst:162 ../../finetuning/finetune.rst:369
#: 2ae2ac9c8e934756b102d61065ea3668 30613a4e3e84444fae06f749bcc9d65c
